		b The torsion tensor (own page)
	p Torsion tensor is
	p \(T_{jk}^i=\Gamma^i_{jk}-\Gamma^i_{kj}\)

	p If torsion is \(0\), then the connection is symmetric.
	h3
		b Basis of tangent space
	p We can use as the basis for tangent space:
	p \(\{\dfrac{(\delta }{\delta x^1})_p,(\dfrac{\delta }{\delta x^2})_p,...\}\)

	p This means we can write a tangent vector as:
	p \(u=u^i(\dfrac{\delta }{\delta x^i})_p\)
	h3
		b Basis of contant space
	p We can use as the basis for the contangent space:
	p \(\{dx^1,dx^2,...\}\)
